label: Lineitem
label_metadata: Description: Finds relevant records based on an Index. Index Scans perform 2 read operations: one to read the index and another to read the actual value from the table.

label: Lineitem*
label_metadata: Description: Filter relation to hold only relevant records.Filter condition: (lineitem.l_shipdate > '1995-03-08'::date)

label: Customer
label_metadata: Description: Finds relevant records by sequentially scanning the input record set. When reading from a table, Seq Scans (unlike Index Scans) perform a single read operation (only the table is read).

label: Customer*
label_metadata: Description: Filter relation to hold only relevant records.Filter condition: (customer.c_mktsegment = 'BUILDING'::bpchar)

label: Orders
label_metadata: Description: Finds relevant records by sequentially scanning the input record set. When reading from a table, Seq Scans (unlike Index Scans) perform a single read operation (only the table is read).

label: Orders*
label_metadata: Description: Filter relation to hold only relevant records.Filter condition: (orders.o_orderdate < '1995-03-08'::date)

label: Customer* ⋈ Orders*
label_metadata: Description: Joins to record sets by hashing one of them (using a Hash Scan).Inner Join with (orders.o_custkey = customer.c_custkey)

label: Lineitem* ⋈ Customer* ⋈ Orders*
label_metadata: Description: Merges two record sets by looping through every record in the first set and trying to find a match in the second set. All matching records are returned.Inner Join

label: AGG
label_metadata:
Description: Groups records together based on a GROUP BY or aggregate function (e.g. sum()).Output: ['lineitem.l_orderkey', "sum((lineitem.l_extendedprice * ('1'::numeric - lineitem.l_discount)))", 'orders.o_orderdate', 'orders.o_shippriority']
Partial Mode: Simple
Strategy: Hashed
Group key: ['lineitem.l_orderkey', 'orders.o_orderdate', 'orders.o_shippriority']

label: LIMIT 10
label_metadata: Description: Returns a specified number of rows from a record set.LIMIT: 10
